article.headline: Binghamton 57, Cornell 56
article.story: VESTAL, N.Y. (AP) -- Lazar Trifunovic made two free throws with 27 seconds left to lead Binghamton over Cornell, 57-56, on Saturday. Trifunovic, a freshman forward from Belgrade, scored 10 of his 12 points in the second half and was fouled as he made an offensive rebound with Binghamton (3-1) trailing 56-55. Cornell missed two shots as the clock wound down. Senior guard Troy Hailey led Binghamton with 15 points, including two three-pointers in the final 2:27. He was four-of-four on three-pointers for the game. Forward Ryan Wittman led Cornell (3-2) with 19 points. Binghamton led 33-30 at the half, the largest lead either team had for the rest of the way.
